    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>The newly emerged Omicron SARS-CoV-2 has 3 distinct sublineages: BA.1, BA.2, and BA.3. BA.1 accounts for the initial surge and is being replaced by BA.2, whereas BA.3 is at a low prevalence at this time. Here we report the neutralization of BNT162b2-vaccinated sera (collected at 1 month after dose 3) against the three Omicron sublineages. To facilitate the neutralization testing, we engineered the complete BA.1, BA.2, or BA.3 spike into an mNeonGreen USA-WA1/2020 SRAS-CoV-2. All BNT162b2-vaccinated sera neutralized USA-WA1/2020, BA.1-, BA.2-, and BA.3-spike SARS-CoV-2s with titers of &gt;20; the neutralization geometric mean titers (GMTs) against the four viruses were 1211, 336, 300, and 190, respectively. Thus, the BA.1-, BA.2-, and BA.3-spike SARS-CoV-2s were 3.6-, 4.0-, and 6.4-fold less efficiently neutralized than the USA-WA1/2020, respectively. Our data have implications in vaccine strategy and understanding the biology of Omicron sublineages.</jats:p>",
